President Muhamamdu Buhari on Wednesday received Antonio Guterres, the United Nations secretary-general, at the presidential villa, Abuja. The UN scribe arrived at the villa at 3:00 pm, where he was welcomed by the president. The two leaders subsequently went into a closed session, where they are expected to deliberate on issues surrounding security and the humanitarian crisis in the north-east and some parts of Nigeria. Guterres is expected to brief state house correspondents at the end of his meeting with the president. The UN secretary-general, who was in Maiduguri, Borno state, on Tuesday, had earlier paid similar visits to neighbouring Niger Republic and Senegal. See photos below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-694695" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403.jpg" alt="" width="1500" height="1000" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403.jpg 1500w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403-768x512.jpg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165403-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-694696" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165400.jpg" alt="" width="1500" height="1000" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165400.jpg 1500w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_165400-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220504_